added.title: Letting Off Steam
added.description: When Thomas and Percy get into their first big fight they're afraid that their friendship is over... until Nia helps them figure out how to resolve it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nia's Perfect Plan
added.description: Nia has volunteered for a big day of deliveries and is determined to make the perfect plan to get it done, but when things start to go awry, she doggedly sticks to her plan and refuses any help.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Caillou's Cross-Hop/Glitter Glitch/The Untidy Classroom
added.description: Caillou doesn't want to hold hands and obey safety rules./Caillou forgets to wash his glittery hands./Caillou complains about having to tidy up.

added.title: No Tradebacks!/Shoe Story/Rollie Racers
added.description: Caillou decides to trade his tiny toy shovel for some stickers./Caillou desperately wants a pair of snazzy light-up sneakers./Rollie Racers (toy cars) are the latest craze.

added.title: Caillou's Song/Follow Me/Where's Caillou?
added.description: Caillou wants to learn to play a song on his little keyboard./Caillou tries to befriend his new classmate, Andy./Caillou wants someone to play with.

added.title: Olive Muddle/Caillou's Clay Play/The Lightning Ball Express
added.description: Grandma brings over some delicious treats./Caillou and Leo accidentally break Rosie's clay poodle./Mrs. Howard brings over an old train set.

added.title: Sarah's Kite/Caillou's New Game/Shiny Reminder
added.description: Caillou flies Sarah's kite and accidentally crashes it into a tree./Caillou has some friends over and they want to play a game./Caillou promises to return Leo's special marker.

added.title: Ice Cream
added.description: It's hot out and Bing and Flop are trying to catch up to Gilly to get some ice cream! Bing finally catches up with Gilly and gets his yummy delicious carroty ice cream. Does he drop his ice cream as he waves goodbye?

added.title: Bandages
added.description: Bing and Coco are nurses today after Coco gets a paper cut on her finger and needs a bandage. But Bing would like a bandage too, and makes one from sticky tape. But what will happen when he tries to take it off and it hurts?

added.title: Cat
added.description: Bing loves playing with Arlo the cat, but what happens when Bing meets a new cat, who isn't so friendly?

added.title: Dandelion
added.description: Bing finds a dandelion in the park and loves blowing the seeds and watching them fly away! He decides to save the last one to give it to Sula, but will he be able to keep the seeds from blowing away in the wind as he takes it to her?

added.title: Voosh
added.description: Bing is vooshing with Hoppity around the garden, and Hoppity is vooshing higher and higher. But what happens when Hoppity vooshes so high that he disappears?

added.title: Lost in Space
added.description: Pocoyo goes to visit his alien friend who wants to show him around his beautiful planet. Pocoyo and the alien have so much fun with the new things that they see and hear that soon they don't know where they are. At first they both panic but Pocoyo realizes with the narrator's and viewers' help that if he tries to remember the last place he was he'll be sure to find his way home.

added.title: Boo!
added.description: Pocoyo has a new game which he enjoys playing on his friends: BOO! Only some of his friends find Pocoyo's game annoying or frightening. But this only encourages Pocoyo more. He boos poor Pato til he ends up a nervous wreck. Elly sees how scared Pato has become and decides to give Pocoyo a taste of his own medicine. Elly makes Pocoyo jump. At first Pocoyo doesn't like it but ultimately Pato and Pocoyo both realize it can be fun to BOO! and to be BOOED!

added.title: Party Pooper
added.description: Pocoyo is having a party and invites all his friends. But instead of letting his friends have fun, Pocoyo keeps bossing them around. Pato, Elly and Fred soon get fed up and leave the party to play their own way. Left to play on his own, Pocoyo realizes that a party with no guests is no fun at all. Pocoyo invites his friends back to the party and everyone has fun playing together in their own unique and individual ways.

added.title: My Pato
added.description: Pato and Elly are arguing over their blocks when Caterpillar and Baby Bird walk past with presents for Pato. Oh no! Pocoyo and Elly have forgotten Pato's birthday. Elly is quick to whisk Pato off to a birthday picnic, determined to prove how much she cares. Not to be outdone, quick-thinking Pocoyo appears at the picnic with a present but Elly retaliates and 'accidentally' breaks it. Pocoyo and Elly fight so hard over Pato that he's almost broken in two. Fed up with all the fight Pato packs his things and is about to leave. When Pocoyo and Elly realize that their fighting has driven Pato away, they quickly make up and turn their efforts into making a special birthday party for Pato.

added.title: Baby Bird Bother
added.description: Baby Bird is in awe of Pocoyo as he plays skillfully with a bouncy ball. Baby Bird continues to admire Pocoyo but this time it's his construction skills as Pocoyo plays with his blocks. And yes, Baby Bird thinks Pocoyo is the best at painting too. At first Pocoyo thinks it's great to have an admirer but soon, Pocoyo can't do anything without Baby Bird interrupting. Eventually Pocoyo gets so frustrated that he sends Baby Bird away. Pocoyo enjoys doing everything all by himself but it's not long before he wonders where his friend Baby Bird has gone. When Pocoyo realizes that Baby Bird was only trying to be his friend Pocoyo decides to invite Baby Bird to a party especially for him.

added.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
added.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

added.title: Popsicle
added.description: Blippi shrinks down and goes on a sweet and exciting adventure through an ice cream truck with Sherry Pop, a fruit popsicle, finding out that she and all frozen treats need to be in the ice-cold so they won't melt.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

added.title: Do You Speak Dance/A New Spider in Town/Dollhouse Mates
added.description: "Maizie" keeps ignoring Lucas and Findley, but not only do they learn she has a cousin, they also learn a new skill!/ Lucas befriends a bright purple toy spider, and Findley gets jealous./ Lucas and Findley move into the dollhouse together.

added.title: Lucas We Have a Problem/Egg-Scuse Me/Pokey Dokey
added.description: Lucas helps Bodhi fulfill her dream of touching a star./ Lucas finds an egg and decides to take care of it. But he learns that responsibility is hard./ When Avocado loses her beloved toy, Lucas and Findley are determined to cheer her up.

added.title: Star Helpers
added.description: Starmush's back is stuck, and the Mushelder has no choice but to ask for help in Mushton. Because Chep is the one that finds a solution to his back problem, Starmush chooses him to help with his daily activities. But Mush-Mush is jealous, he would have loved being the chosen one…

added.title: Finders Keepers
added.description: When Dibble loses her beloved playball, the Care Bears are shocked to discover it has been taken by the Keeper, a mysterious figure who collects and stores away all items lost in the Silver Lining. To regain possession of the ball, the Bears and Dibble must help the Keeper recover a loss of his own.

added.title: Puff's Perfect Picnic
added.description: Because he has won the moss-ball game last year, Puff is in charge of organizing this Summer's Picnic. Only Puff isn't comfortable in that role. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit offer to help and make sure all the Mushables will follow Puff's lead. Gradually, Puff gains confidence and ends up bossing everyone around. Now, all the Mushables are about to flee the Picnic!

added.title: The Incredible Shrinking Bears
added.description: Frustrated that she's too small to reach even the bottom-most berries on a tree, Dibble becomes the tallest member of the team when a strange cloud of magical fog shrinks the Care Bears to miniature size. To save them, she must race against time to get them to a reversal-fog that will return them to their normal size.

added.title: Who's Your Granny?
added.description: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities.

added.title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
added.description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

added.title: Act Your Age
added.description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

added.title: Loose Change
added.description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

added.title: Wise Quacker
added.description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

added.title: Gravity
added.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

removed.title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
removed.description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

removed.title: Rise and Funshine
removed.description: Funshine learns he can be as fearless as one of his super hero comic book characters when the Team falls into a magical sleep. To awaken them, he must transport them in the Cloudseeker to a special place in the Silver Lining - but he has never driven it before, and must learn from a comical "How To Pilot the Cloudseeker" video hosted by Grumpy.

removed.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
removed.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

removed.title: Mind Your Manners
removed.description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

removed.title: Whistle Woes
removed.description: When Thomas's whistle suddenly stops working, he learns that he doesn't need his whistle to still be himself.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Not in My Backyard
removed.description: Pocoyo discovers some old rubbish and decides to have a clear out. Baby Bird, Pato and Elly do the same. Soon there's a huge pile of rubbish, and it turns out it's on Caterpillar's doorstep. The rubbish keeps getting thrown around until finally Pocoyo follows the rubbish and realizes it's just going in a circle. In order to break the cycle, Pocoyo helps his friends make some new fun toys and games out of the rubbish.

removed.title: Vamoosh on the Loosh
removed.description: Pocoyo promises to teach Baby Bird to drive the Vamoosh but keeps putting it off. Fed up, Baby Bird decides to have a go on his own but he doesn't know how. The Vamoosh spins out of control. Pocoyo realises he must keep to his promise and teach Baby Bird to drive properly.

removed.title: Skateboard
removed.description: Bing and Flop are in the park when Pando vooshes past on his skatebaord. Pando agrees to let Bing try out his skateboard. But what happens when Bing comes to a steep hill and the skateboard goes faster and faster?

removed.title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
removed.description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

removed.title: A Pastime for Petunia
removed.description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

removed.title: Scooter Madness
removed.description: Pocoyo and Pato find Elly's scooter and decide to take it back to her. Pato enjoys showing off his scooter skills and quickly forgets who it belongs to. Pato's scooter tricks get bigger and bigger until eventually he breaks the scooter into pieces. Pocoyo and Pato try to fix the scooter but it's no good. However will they tell Elly? At first they try to cover up what they've done but eventually they have to confess. Thankfully Elly is not upset with them as she has another scooter and is just pleased her friends told the truth in the end.

removed.title: Butterfly
removed.description: Bing and his friends are playing at Amma's today when a beautiful butterfly comes inside. But what happens when Bing catches the butterfly in his hands while trying to save it?

removed.title: Scary Noises
removed.description: Pocoyo and Pato are out for an adventure in the Vamoosh but have to land on a strange planet when a part of the Vamoosh falls off. Whilst searching for the missing part, Pato gets scared because he hears a strange, scary noise. They both realize there is nothing to be scared of and the alien just wants to make friends.

removed.title: Boingo/Findley's Bad Day/You Rang
removed.description: Lucas, Findley and Bodhi become obsessed with a new toy called Boingo./ Findley is convinced House is out to get him./ Arlo is missing his mother, so Lucas gives him a bell to ring if he needs Lucas's help - bad idea.

removed.title: Rainy Boots
removed.description: It's a wet, drippy day and Bing has his rainy boots on to help Flop take the trash out. While splish splashing outside, what will happen when Bing does a BIG SPLASH and finds his rainy boots have holes in them?

removed.title: Bouncing Back
removed.description: Mush-Mush is very proud he invented a new game called Fruity Bounce, where he and his friends bounce as high as possible on the bouncier fruits they can find. Little did he know, the Mushups were fruit-bouncing way before he, Chep and Lilit did. So, Mush-Mush decides that if he can't be the inventor of the game, he'll at least be the best at it. Mushlers vs Mushups, game on!

removed.title: Morel in the Dark
removed.description: When Mush-Mush discovers that Morel is afraid of the dark, he suggests that Chep, Lilit and he take the Mushlets to their first overnight forest camp. Morel is relieved. But when Mush-Mush and his friends later come back, panicked, and reveal that the Mushlets have disappeared, Morel has no choice but to face his fear and join our friends on their rescue mission in the dark!

removed.title: Pouting Match
removed.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

removed.title: Potato
removed.description: Bing and Sula find a potato with a nose on it in Amma's garden, and they want to keep it. So they call it Nosey. But, what will happen when they show Nosey how to go down the slide?

removed.title: Let Them Make Cake
removed.description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

removed.title: Bye Bye Bee/Jeepers Peepers/House is Breathing
removed.description: Saying goodbye can be hard, but there are ways to feel close to your friends./ Can Dimples finally beat Weebscuit at a staring competition?/ Lucas is convinced House is alive when the heating vent comes on.

removed.title: Detective Pocoyo
removed.description: Elly is aghast to realize that her darling doll is missing. Detective Pocoyo decides to help Elly and he looks for clues as to where her doll might be. While Pocoyo goes back to the scene of the crime, Elly finds that she had her doll all along: it wasn't lost at all, she'd simply mislaid it. Elly is too embarrassed to own up and tells Pocoyo she doesn't need her doll anymore. But Detective Pocoyo uncovers the truth and the mystery is solved.

removed.title: Chalk Dinosaur
removed.description: Bing wants to draw a big picture so Flop finds him some chalk to draw on the sidewalk outside their house. But what happens when a big rain cloud comes just as Bing's finished his chalk dinosaur?

removed.title: Wonderful World
removed.description: Nia shows Thomas and Diesel how much unique beauty exists in Sodor, which comes in handy when they need plants to beautify a Plaza in Vicarstown.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Road Trip
removed.description: On a mission to a remote area of the Silver Lining, Cheer questions the directions from Bedtime's maps. Everyone else backs Bedtime: he's never been wrong before! When the directions turn out to be wrong and lead them into danger, Cheer must trust her instincts to find a way out of the mess.
